<section class="transparent-car">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
			<article class="leadership-slider">
			  <!-- main container -->
			  <div class="carousel" id="carousel-example-captions" data-ride="carousel">
				<!-- tabs (converted from bullet icons to text tabs) -->
				<ol class="carousel-indicators" style="">
				  <li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="0" class=""><a href="#">Secure Interfaces</a></li>
				  <li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="1" class=""><a href="#">Secure Gateway</a></li>
				  <li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="2" class="active"><a href="#">Secure Networks</a></li>
				  <li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="3" class=""><a href="#">Secure Processors</a></li>
				  <li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="4" class=""><a href="#">Secure Car Access</a></li>
				</ol>
			 
				<!-- Inner content grouping the various slides -->
				<div class="carousel-inner" role="listbox">
				  <!-- icon links on images -->
				  <ul class="carousel-indicators-icons list-unstyled">
					<li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="0" class="">
					  <a class="nav-icon" href=""><span class="icon-toggle"></span></a>
					</li>
					<li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="1" class="">
					  <a class="nav-icon" href=""><span class="icon-toggle"></span></a>
					</li>
					<li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="2" class="active">
					  <a class="nav-icon" href=""><span class="icon-toggle"></span></a>
					</li>
					<li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="3" class="">
					  <a class="nav-icon" href=""><span class="icon-toggle"></span></a>
					</li>
					<li data-target="#carousel-example-captions" data-slide-to="4" class="">
					  <a class="nav-icon" href=""><span class="icon-toggle"></span></a>
					</li>
				  </ul>
			 
				  <!-- First Item -->
				  <div class="item">
					<figure class="item-image">
					  <img class="img-responsive" alt="First Image" src="/assets/images/en/banners/Security-TransparentCar-02-Layer1-Interface.jpg" data-holder-rendered="true" />
					</figure>
			 
					<div class="item-content">
					  <div class="carousel-caption">
						<h3 class="carousel-title">Secure Interfaces</h3>
						<p>A vehicle’s communication interfaces connect the car and its occupants to the outside world. These channels need to be protected to protect user privacy and vehicle safety. Our Secure Interfaces layer uses strong encryption and authentication to ensure that the vehicle is communicating with known (trusted) entities only and that received data can be trusted.</p>
					  </div>
					</div>
				  </div>
				  <!-- Second Item -->
				  <div class="item">
					<figure class="item-image">
					  <img class="img-responsive" alt="First Image" src="/assets/images/en/banners/Security-TransparentCar-03-Layer2-Gateway.jpg" data-holder-rendered="true" />
					</figure>
			 
					<div class="item-content">
					  <div class="carousel-caption">
						<h3 class="carousel-title">Secure Gateway</h3>
						<p>Our Secure Gateway layer acts as a firewall that controls access from the external interfaces (such as the internet) to the vehicle’s inner network, and that controls which nodes in the vehicle’s network can communicate with each other. As such, it provides domain isolation between e.g. infotainment systems and safety-critical systems. It also converts between the different automotive communication protocols.</p>
					  </div>
					</div>
				  </div>
			 
				  <!-- Third Item (Middle Active) -->
				  <div class="item active">
					<figure class="item-image">
					  <img class="img-responsive" alt="First Image" src="/assets/images/en/banners/Security-TransparentCar-04-Layer3-Networks.jpg" data-holder-rendered="true" />
					</figure>
			 
					<div class="item-content">
					  <div class="carousel-caption">
						<h3 class="carousel-title">Secure Network</h3>
						<p>Our Secure Networks layer protects the communication over the various in-vehicle networks against data manipulation and data theft by adding message authentication and by encrypting data. It also provides intrusion detection capabilities for detecting anomalies in the network traffic.</p>
					  </div>
					</div>
				  </div>
			 
				  <!-- Fourth Item -->
				  <div class="item">
					<figure class="item-image">
					  <img class="img-responsive" alt="First Image" src="/assets/images/en/banners/Security-TransparentCar-05-Layer4-Processors.jpg" data-holder-rendered="true" />
					</figure>
			 
					<div class="item-content">
					  <div class="carousel-caption">
						<h3 class="carousel-title">Secure Processors</h3>
						<p>ECUs continuously generate, process, exchange, and store large amounts of potentially sensitive data—making them an attractive target for hackers. NXP’s broad portfolio of automotive microcontrollers and processors feature dedicated automotive (SHE and HSM) security modules that protect software from being manipulated and that support secure software updates and data protection.</p>
					  </div>
					</div>
				  </div>
			 
				  <!-- Fifth Item -->
				  <div class="item">
					<figure class="item-image">
					  <img class="img-responsive" alt="First Image" src="/assets/images/en/banners/Security-TransparentCar-Plus1-CarAccess.jpg" data-holder-rendered="true" />
					</figure>
			 
					<div class="item-content">
					  <div class="carousel-caption">
						<h3 class="carousel-title">Secure Car Access</h3>
						<p>Our “+1” layer for Secure Car Access provides traditional physical vehicle protection through anti-theft immobilizer and smart car access functions. Innovations in this area include new features like remote lock & unlock, passive start, remote vehicle monitoring, and car access using a smart phone or smartkey device.</p>
					  </div>
					</div>
				  </div>
				</div>
			 
				<!-- Previous and Next Controls -->
				<!--a href="#carousel-example-captions" class="left carousel-control" role="button" data-slide="prev">
				  <span class="icon-arrow-left" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				  <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
				</a>
			 
				<a href="#carousel-example-captions" class="right carousel-control" role="button" data-slide="next">
				  <span class="icon-arrow-right2" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				  <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
				</a-->
			  </div>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
<!-- /.Transparent car -->

 <!-- SECTION Ecosystem -->
<a name="section-ecosystem"></a>
<section class="ecosystem color-scheme-medium-grey">
                
    <div class="row marg-bot-4x hideme">
        <div class="col-lg-5 col-lg-push-5 col-lg-offset-1">
			<div class="overlay">
				<a href="/applications/solutions-for-the-iot-and-adas/automotive/secure-vehicle-architecture/v2x-communications:V2X-COMMUNICATIONS" target="_blank" class="dtmGenLink" data-dtmName="SECURE INTERFACES - Image Link">
					<div class="img-heading">
						<img class="img-responsive" src="/assets/images/en/banners/Security-Complete.jpg" alt="SECURE INTERFACES" />
					</div>
				</a>
			</div>
        </div>      
        <div class="col-lg-5 col-lg-pull-5">
            <h3 class="subtitle">SECURE INTERFACES</h3>
            <p>
				This layer protects the communications to and from vehicles, using secure elements as a tamper proof trust anchors. 
			</p>
			<a href="/applications/solutions-for-the-iot-and-adas/automotive/secure-vehicle-architecture/v2x-communications:V2X-COMMUNICATIONS" target="_blank" class="dtmGenLink" data-dtmName="SECURE INTERFACES - Read Whitepaper Button"><div class="btn">Learn More</div></a>
